# Owner-scoped dive data

Source: **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/owasp_access_control_policy.md`** (§2.1, §3).

## Do

- Filter `@Query`, `FetchDescriptor`, and list builders with **`ownerProfileID == currentProfile.id`** (or equivalent signed-in owner).
- Assign ownership via existing helpers (`DiveActivityOwnership`, buddy/trip/equipment/cert helpers) when inserting user rows.
- Prefer passing **owner UUID / `PersistentIdentifier`**, not assuming “all rows on device are mine.”
- Keep catalog reads (`MarineLife`, reference `DiveSite`) on the **catalog** store — do not mix into owner-scoped user queries.

## Do not

- Add unscoped fetches of dives, media, sightings, buddies, or trips for production UI “because the device only has one user.”
- Use **Firebase UID** for `ownerProfileID` or dive ownership.
- Expand **`claimUnowned*`** / orphan adoption without going through **`DiveUnownedClaimGate`**. Default policy: claim only when **no other profile** already owns dives/buddies on the device (`force:` is tests / explicit migration only).
- Show another profile’s rows in Logbook / Home / Search / export without an explicit multi-profile product design.

```swift
// ✅ Scoped
#Predicate<DiveActivity> { $0.ownerProfileID == ownerID }

// ❌ Unscoped owner data for a signed-in screen
FetchDescriptor<DiveActivity>()
```
